Interface IndexDiff

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ThreeWayIndexDiff
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IndexDiffImpl, ThreeWayIndexDiffImpl

    public interface IndexDiff
extends Serializable
    Represents an index difference between two index commits.

      • contains

        boolean contains(long key)
        Returns true if the diff contains the given key, otherwise false.

        More formally, it returns with true only and if only one of the followings are true:

        • #getNewIds()#contains(key)
        • #getChangedIds()#contains(key)
        • #getDetachedIds()#contains(key)
        Parameters:
        key - the key to check.
        Returns:
        true if the diff contains the key, otherwise false.
